{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"]]},"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/categorizing-and-organizing-data-with-content-tags"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Identify topics, actions, objects, and emotions in input text with a content tagging model."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Foundation Models"}],"title":"Categorizing and organizing data with content tags","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Foundation Models framework provides an adapted on-device system language"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"model that specializes in content tagging. A content tagging model produces"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a list of categorizing tags based on the input text you provide. When you prompt"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the content tagging model, it produces a tag that uses one to a few lowercase"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"words. The model finds the similarity between the terms in your prompt so tags","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are semantically consistent. For example, the model produces the topic tag","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“greet” when it encounters words such as “hi,” “hello,” and “yo”. Use the content"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tagging model to:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gather statistics about popular topics and opinions in a social app."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Customize your app’s experience by matching tags to a person’s interests."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Help people organize their content for tasks such as email autolabeling using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the tags your app detects."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Identify trends by aggregating tags across your content.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re tagging content that’s not an action, object, emotion, or topic, use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase/general","type":"reference"},{"text":" instead. Use the general model to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"generate content like hashtags for social media posts. If you adopt the tool","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calling API, and want to generate tags, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase/general","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and pass the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" output to the content tagging model. For more information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"about tool-calling, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/expanding-generation-with-tool-calling","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Provide instructions to the model","anchor":"Provide-instructions-to-the-model","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The content tagging model isn’t a typical language model that responds to a query","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from a person: instead, it evaluates and groups the input you provide. For example,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if you ask the model questions, it produces tags about asking questions. Before","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you prompt the model, consider the instructions you want it to follow: instructions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the the model produce a more precise outcome than instructions in the prompt."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The model identifies topics, actions, objects, and emotions from the input text","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you provide, so include the type of tags you want in your instructions. It’s also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"helpful to provide the number of tags you want the model to produce. You can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"also specify the number of elements in your instructions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["// Create an instance of the on-device language model's content tagging use case.","let model = SystemLanguageModel(useCase: .contentTagging)","","// Initialize a session with the model and instructions.","let session = LanguageModelSession(model: model, instructions: \"\"\"","    Provide the two tags that are most significant in the context of topics.","    \"\"\"",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You don’t need to provide a lot of custom tagging instructions; the content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tagging model respects the output format you want, even in the absence of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instructions. If you create a generable data type that describes properties"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GenerationGuide"},{"type":"text","text":", you can save context window space by not including"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"custom instructions. If you don’t provide generation guides, the model generates"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"topic-related tags by default."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For very short input queries, topic and emotion tagging instructions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"provide the best results. Actions or object lists will be too specific, and may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"repeat the words in the query.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Create-a-generable-type","type":"heading","text":"Create a generable type"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The content tagging model supports ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Generable"},{"text":", so you can define a custom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"data type that the model uses when generating a response. Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GenerationGuide/maximumCount(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on your generable type to enforce a maximum number of tags that you want the model","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to return. The code below uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Generable"},{"text":" guide descriptions to specify the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"kinds and quantities of tags the model produces:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@Generable","struct ContentTaggingResult {","    @Guide(","        description: \"Most important actions in the input text.\",","        .maximumCount(2)","    )","    let actions: [String]","","    @Guide(","        description: \"Most important emotions in the input text.\",","        .maximumCount(3)","    )","    let emotions: [String]","","    @Guide(","        description: \"Most important objects in the input text.\",","        .maximumCount(5)","    )","    let objects: [String]","","    @Guide(","        description: \"Most important topics in the input text.\",","        .maximumCount(2)","    )","    let topics: [String]","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ideally, match the maximum count you use in your instructions with what you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"define using the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GenerationGuide/maximumCount(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" generation guide. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"use a different maximum for each, consider putting the larger maximum in your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instructions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Long queries can produce a large number of actions and objects, so define a maximum","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"count to limit the number of tags. This step helps the model focus on the most"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"relevant parts of long queries, avoids duplicate actions and objects, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"improves decoding time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you have a complex set of constraints on tagging that are more complicated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than the maximum count support of the tagging model, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase/general","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For more information on guided generation, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Generate a content tagging response","level":2,"anchor":"Generate-a-content-tagging-response","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Initialize your session by using the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase/contentTagging","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"model:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["// Create an instance of the model with the content tagging use case.","let model = SystemLanguageModel(useCase: .contentTagging)","","","// Initialize a session with the model.","let session = LanguageModelSession(model: model)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The code below prompts the model to respond about a picnic at the beach with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tags like “outdoor activity,” “beach,” and “picnic”:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let prompt = \"\"\"","    Today we had a lovely picnic with friends at the beach.","    \"\"\"","let response = try await session.respond(","    to: prompt,","    generating: ContentTaggingResult.self",")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The prompt “Grocery list: 1. Bread flour 2. Salt 3. Instant yeast” prompts the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model to respond with the topic “grocery shopping” and includes the objects","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“grocery list” and “bread flour”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For some queries, lists may produce the same tag. For example, some topic and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"emotion tags, like humor, may overlap. When the model produces duplicates,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"handle it in code, and choose the tag you prefer. When you reuse the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", the model may produce tags related to the previous turn"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or a combination of turns. The model produces what it views as the most important."}]}]}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/foundationmodels/categorizing-and-organizing-data-with-content-tags"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Use cases","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"],"anchor":"Use-cases","generated":true}],"references":{"foundation-models-framework-landing-PageImage-card.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"foundation-models-framework-landing-PageImage-card.png","variants":[{"traits":["2x","light"],"url":"https://docs-assets.developer.apple.com/published/274bdf69903b6dd606f05b29f5e08f04/foundation-models-framework-landing-PageImage-card%402x.png"},{"traits":["2x","dark"],"url":"https://docs-assets.developer.apple.com/published/0fc8245c5e8046f5efab6bfe0e1be692/foundation-models-framework-landing-PageImage-card~dark%402x.png"}],"alt":"An illustration that represents a foundation model."},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool","title":"Tool","url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/tool","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A tool that a model can call to gather information at runtime or perform side effects.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Tool"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Tool","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create robust apps by describing output you want programmatically."}],"title":"Generating Swift data structures with guided generation"},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/Foundatio